"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-02-olympics-2024-badminton-nigerias-opeyori-crashes-out\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's Anuoluwapo Opeyori is out of the men's Paris 2024 Olympic Badminton event.  This was possible after he lost 0-2 to the world's number six, Li Shifeng of China on Thursday.  Opeyori made his Chinese opponent work hard for every point earned during the match.  He lost 17-21, 17-21 against Li Shifeng.  The defeat was his second loss in the Group N of the men's singles event.  Recall that Opeyori was defeated by Tobias Kuenzi of Switzerland at Le Chapelle Arena on Wednesday.  Serie A: Leao backs Chukwueze to shine for AC Milan  EPL: You can not qualify for Champions League like this - Gallas tells Chelsea  Paris 2024: Opeyori stumbles in badminton opener vs Switzerland's Kuenzi  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria captain, Opeyori ready to conquer  badminton opponent  Paris 2024: Amusan named Team Nigeria's flag bearer, Opeyori captain  Nigeria shine at Badminton Championship in Cairo as Opeyori retains African title  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"